Halong Bay - One of the Seven Wonders of the World
Aug 2013 ‚Ä¢ Couples
We took a one night trip to Halong Bay on board the Phoenix Cruiser. What a treat! It is an old boat, but luxurious and very comfortable. The staff on board couldn't have been friendlier or nicer to all the passengers. Especially our tour guide Hoa. Nothing was too much bother for her.
The food on board was 'to die for' and there was no shortage of it. Activities were planned for the duration of the cruise, but one could choose to opt out of the activities if they chose. A cooking demonstration that involved everyone, was held on the morning of our departure, and it was a lot of fun. All the passengers got involved and there were lots of laughs. I would highly recommend this particular boat and cruise. We'll be going again.
RooGoneWild
