Halongsapa tour - Calypso Cruise 2D1N
Oct 2012 ‚Ä¢ Couples
We booked our boat through Halongsapa tours (located near the lake in the old quarter) and were very pleased we did.
The trip to and around Halong Bay followed our trip to Sapa. The Calypso cruise was very nice. The cabins were spacious and clean with good facilities. The food was great and the scenery, caves, kayaking and karaoke were all fantastic.The bay itself was lovely. Yes, there are other boats, but you do not need to concentrate on them. The cruise is quite regimented, but in order to do so much, it probably needs to be.
Halongsapa tours proved to be excellent. They escorted us to trains, looked after our luggage, collected us, booked taxis for us, took us for breakfast... all in all much more than was expected! Both Cham and Tien were very friendly and we enjoyed talking to them.
If we were to go again, perhaps we would book the 3D2N option.
